fields.label: You have been injured in a motor accident. This is what you should do now.

groups.label: • You want someone to help you recover.
Were you on the way to work, or on the way home from work:
Where did the accident happen? (Give crossroads if you were at a corner):
Were any of the cars involved registered in another state?:
Please give the Names and Addresses of the drivers involved and also all vehicle registration numbers, your car first.
When & how did the accident occur?
And what happened to the patient's body during the accident.?
Symptoms at the time of presentation.
Observations. E.G. Walks with a limp, anxious, pleasant, etc.
Medication and any other Office performed procedures.
MVA W/ C Acquaintance form O January 1999 by Gaion Moad

fields.label: • Tell the police as soon as possible. Go to your local police station to do this, you can also do the report online www.crashreport.com.au

groups.label: • Ring the Motor Vehicle Personal injury Division on 9264 3333 and ask them for a claim form and claim number. This will allow your medical costs to be paid by the insurers, provided the accident was not your fault.
• You may need some advice in dealing with the aspects of your claim. We can help here.
• You may need help from other doctor's, or from physiotherapists. We choose them carefully to suit your needs.
• Accidents or injuries, especially noting those involving claims.
• Current employment (& work history where relevant). How long in this job?
• Since the accident and prior to presentation.
Workers' Compensation Certificates. Fitness for work status.
Tick one box. Show period in days or weeks as appropriate, or from date.
What are we going to do when the patient returns?
Continuing or stopping current treatments, or other regimes.
